0 CHEVALIER~
&w
CHEVALIER

Warriors who have trained to ride upon mounts while in combat, they are 
held to a high standard of personal moral code which is passed among them 
through training and word of mouth. Chevaliers can handle combat when off 
of their mounts, but since their fighting style integrates the use of a 
mount into most everything they do, it is at a disadvantage. They are 
usually proficient with long blades above other weapons, and do not tend 
to know magic. They are quite skilled in medicine, the care of their 
mounts, and the art of discourse. Like Clerics, Chevaliers tend to travel 
a lot.

Persons of races that are mountable, or usually those that have hooves, 
cannot be chevaliers in the traditional sense, since they lack the ability 
to mount other creatures. However, such creatures usually have the ability 
to develop the skills of a Lancer.

~

