0 ROGUE~
&w
ROGUE

Not all Rogues are versed in the dark arts of deception, but it is
typically  associated with persons of their persuasion. Generally trained
in the use of  light, concealable and ranged weapons, rogues aim to make
certain that combat  will never distract them from their other business
for long. Their style is to be quick and deadly, more for their own
benefit than those they come up  against. Not all rogues are wholly
reliant upon physical weapons, but not many tend toward magical studies.
Those that do usually are more interested in the  use of already existing
magical items or base magical potions to further their  ends. A subtle
weapon is an effective one. They therefore often learn the  magical ritual
for detecting and examining magical influences, and are also  usually
skilled at herbcraft, forgery, medicine and law. One must know what  is
legal to the letter if one wishes to protect ones innocence when it is, 
invariably, questioned. Not all rogues are of the light build so commonly 
associated to the stereotype, but very few rogues choose to wear armor
more  obvious in its nature than leather.
 
~

